);","strongs_def":"renewal (figuratively)","kjv_def":"newness","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"newness(2x)"},"G2595":{"id":"G2595","lemma":"κάρφος","translit":"kárphos","derivation":"from (to wither);","strongs_def":"a dry twig or straw","kjv_def":"mote","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"mote(6x)"},"G2521":{"id":"G2521","lemma":"κάθημαι","translit":"káthēmai","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά);","strongs_def":"and (to sit; akin to the base of G1476 (ἑδραῖος)); to sit down; figuratively, to remain, reside","kjv_def":"dwell, sit (by, down)","pos":"verb","usage":"sit(82x), dwell(1x)"},"G2591":{"id":"G2591","lemma":"Κάρπος","translit":"Kárpos","derivation":"perhaps for G2590 (καρπός);","strongs_def":"Carpus, probably a Christian","kjv_def":"Carpus"},"G2568":{"id":"G2568","lemma":"Καλοὶ Λιμένες","translit":"Kaloì Liménes","derivation":"plural of G2570 (καλός) and G3040 (λιμήν);","strongs_def":"Good Harbors, i.e. Fairhaven, a bay of Crete","kjv_def":"fair havens","pos":"proper locative noun"},"G2508":{"id":"G2508","lemma":"καθαίρω","translit":"kathaírō","derivation":"from G2513 (καθαρός);","strongs_def":"to cleanse, i.e. (specially) to prune; figuratively, to expiate","kjv_def":"purge","pos":"verb","usage":"purge(2x)"},"G2573":{"id":"G2573","lemma":"καλῶς","translit":"kalōs","derivation":"adverb from G2570 (καλός);","strongs_def":"well (usually morally)","kjv_def":"(in a) good (place), honestly, + recover, (full) well","pos":"adverb","usage":"well(30x), good(2x)"},"G2519":{"id":"G2519","lemma":"καθηγητής","translit":"kathēgētḗs","derivation":"from a compound of G2596 (κατά) and G2233 (ἡγέομαι);","strongs_def":"a guide, i.e. (figuratively) a teacher","kjv_def":"master","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"master(3x)"},"G2517":{"id":"G2517","lemma":"καθεξῆς","translit":"kathexēs","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G1836 (ἑξῆς);","strongs_def":"thereafter, i.e. consecutively; as a noun (by ellipsis of noun) a subsequent person or time","kjv_def":"after(-ward), by (in) order","pos":"adverb","usage":"afterward(1x), after(1x)"},"G2507":{"id":"G2507","lemma":"καθαιρέω","translit":"kathairéō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G138 (αἱρέομαι) (including its alternate);","strongs_def":"to lower (or with violence) demolish (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"cast (pull, put, take) down, destroy","pos":"verb","usage":"destroy(2x)"},"G2578":{"id":"G2578","lemma":"κάμπτω","translit":"kámptō","derivation":"apparently a primary verb;","strongs_def":"to bend","kjv_def":"bow","pos":"verb","usage":"bow(4x)"},"G2598":{"id":"G2598","lemma":"καταβάλλω","translit":"katabállō","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G906 (βάλλω);","strongs_def":"to throw down","kjv_def":"cast down, lay","pos":"verb","usage":"lay(1x)"},"G2534":{"id":"G2534","lemma":"καίγε","translit":"kaíge","derivation":"from G2532 (καί) and G1065 (γέ);","strongs_def":"and at least (or even, indeed)","kjv_def":"and, at least","pos":"conjunction","usage":"also(1x)"},"G2576":{"id":"G2576","lemma":"καμμύω","translit":"kammýō","derivation":"from a compound of G2596 (κατά) and the base of G3466 (μυστήριον);","strongs_def":"to shut down, i.e. close the eyes","kjv_def":"close","pos":"verb","usage":"close(2x)"},"G2516":{"id":"G2516","lemma":"καθέζομαι","translit":"kathézomai","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and the base of G1476 (ἑδραῖος);","strongs_def":"to sit down","kjv_def":"sit","pos":"verb","usage":"sit(6x)"},"G2572":{"id":"G2572","lemma":"καλύπτω","translit":"kalýptō","derivation":"akin to G2813 (κλέπτω) and G2928 (κρύπτω);","strongs_def":"to cover up (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"cover, hide","pos":"verb","usage":"cover(5x), hide(3x)"},"G2522":{"id":"G2522","lemma":"καθημερινός","translit":"kathēmerinós","derivation":"from G2596 (κατά) and G2250 (ἡμέρα);","strongs_def":"quotidian","kjv_def":"daily","pos":"adjective","usage":"daily(1x)"},"G2585":{"id":"G2585","lemma":"καπηλεύω","translit":"kapēleúō","derivation":"from (a huckster);","strongs_def":"to retail, i.e. (by implication) to adultera